Class FuzzyCompleteEvaluationStoppingCondition

  com.pedroalmir.athena.impl.fuzzy.stoppingCondition.FuzzyCompleteEvaluationStoppingCondition
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.google.common.base.Predicate<Algorithm>, StoppingCondition<Algorithm>, java.lang.Cloneable
public class FuzzyCompleteEvaluationStoppingCondition
extends java.lang.Object
implements StoppingCondition<Algorithm>

A stopping condition which uses measurements to determine if an algorithm has completed e.g. MeasuredStoppingCondition(new Iterations(), new Maximum(), 1000) will stop an algorithm once the number of iterations is greater than or equal to 1000, MeasuredStoppingCondition(new Diversity(), new Minimum(), 0.01) stops it when the population's diversity is less than or equal to 0.01, etc.
